{
 "cells": [
  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "# Gaudin ODE solver (gl(4), two-site, [S,S,0,0] x [P,P,0,0])\n\nSelf-contained solver for the gl(4) Gaudin oper (the $h\\to0$ scaling limit of the XXX Baxter\nequation), derived and verified in `baxter_SU4_L2_XXX.wb`. Only the pieces needed to run the\nsolver are copied here: the tensor-product decomposition, the output-irrep Casimirs/Q-degrees,\nthe hardcoded 4th-order Gaudin ODE (in terms of the abstract Casimirs `C2,C4`), and the\ngauge-fixed polynomial solver. No XXX transfer matrices / Baxter difference equation here --\nsee the source notebook for that derivation.\n\nSites fixed at $w_1=0,w_2=1$.",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 1,
   "value": "Tensor-product decomposition [S,S,0,0] x [P,P,0,0] for gl(4) via Schur polynomials ---\n   The gl(4) character of irrep lam is the Schur polynomial s_lam(x1..x4) (Weyl bialternant).\n   Since s_lam s_mu = Sum_nu c^nu_{lam mu} s_nu, the irreps nu in the tensor product are exactly\n   those in the product's Schur expansion; c^nu = Littlewood-Richardson multiplicity. Decompose\n   by peeling off the lex-highest monomial (a dominant highest weight) with its coefficient.",
   "languageId": "markdown",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "ClearAll[schur, tensorDecomp, dimGL4, irreps];\n\n(*schur polynomial in x[1],x[2],x[3],x[4]*)\nschur[lam_, x_List] := Cancel[Det[Table[x[[i]]^(lam[[j]] + Length[x] - j), {i, Length[x]}, {j, Length[x]}]]/Det[Table[x[[i]]^(Length[x] - j), {i, Length[x]}, {j, Length[x]}]]];\n\n\n(*dimension of the representation lam = {λ1,λ2,λ3,λ4}*)\ndimGL4[lam_] := Product[(lam[[i]] - lam[[j]] + j - i)/(j - i), {i, 4}, {j, i + 1, 4}];\n\n(*decompose the tensor product λ x μ into irreps*)\ntensorDecomp[lam_, mu_] := Module[{x = Array[xx, 4], prod, rules, nu, mult, out = {}},\n   prod = Expand[schur[lam, x] schur[mu, x]];\n   While[prod =!= 0, rules = Association[CoefficientRules[prod, x]]; nu = Last[Sort[Keys[rules]]];\n     mult = rules[nu]; AppendTo[out, nu -> mult]; prod = Expand[prod - mult schur[nu, x]]];\n   out];\n\n(* the irreps mu (all multiplicity 1 for this family) appearing in [S,S,0,0] x [P,P,0,0] *)\nirreps[S_, P_] := tensorDecomp[{S, S, 0, 0}, {P, P, 0, 0}][[All, 1]];",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [],
   "metadata": {}
  },
  {
   "kind": 2,
   "value": "(*example - all irreps appearing in the tensor product of [2,2,0,0] x [3,3,0,0]*)\nirreps[2,3]",
   "languageId": "wolfram",
   "outputs": [
    {
     "items": [
      {
